title: South Korean teachers rally after colleague’s death
description: Teachers in South Korea protested in support of better protection laws after one was found deceased in an apparent suicide after suffering anxiety over complaints by a parent.

title: Deadly floods tear through central Spain after torrential rainfall
description: At least two people died as record rainfall caused heavy flooding in central Spain, shutting roads, subway lines and high-speed train connections, authorities said.

title: WATCH: Emotional scenes as Pope Francis leaves Mongolia
description: Pope Francis wrapped up the first-ever papal visit to Mongolia on Monday by inaugurating a new church-run homeless clinic and shelter.

title: Subway, train lines and roads closed in Spain after heavy rain
description: A few subway lines in Madrid and high-speed train connections with southern cities were closed on Monday morning and two men were missing after torrential rain hit central Spain.

title: Miss Universe Indonesia contestants speak out about sexual harassment claims
description: Contestants in this year’s Miss Universe Indonesia pageant are speaking out about sexual harassment they say they were subjected to by local organizers.

title: Zelenskyy moves to replace Ukraine's defense minister
description: Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelenskyy said on Sunday he had decided to dismiss Defense Minister Oleksii Reznikov from his post and would seek to replace him with Rustem Umerov, head of Ukraine’s main privatization fund.

title: Biden says he’s disappointed that China's Xi won't attend G20 summit
description: President Joe Biden said on Sunday that he was disappointed that Chinese President Xi Jinping was not attending the summit of G20 leaders in India, but added that he was going to “get to see him.”

title: South Korean teachers to rally after colleague’s death
description: South Korean teachers are set to rally on Monday to demand better protection of their rights and to protest what they say is harassment by overbearing parents.
